Female
Wings slightly longer than FWs (see 
Table 9
); brown, their veins yellowish. FW venation: 3 anal veins, CuP and CuA bifurcated twice each (
Fig. 8G
); MP close to CuA on lateral field, and R bifurcated 8 times; transverse veins numerous, as strong as longitudinal veins, but fainter between anal veins.
